Description:
Annotation on the envelope: "Rubens Herkules und Omphale" addressed to "Herrn Professor Dr. phil. Hans Gerh. Evers 6101 Traisa üb. Darmstadt Waldstr. 43"

  • Extracts from different publications
  • Bibliographic references
  • Essay: 'La découverte et l'histoire d'une œuvre inconnue de Rubens', in "L'Amour de l'art", 9, Nov. 1937

The inventory of 1993 also mentions reproductions, but these are missing and were probably taken out in the Rubenianum and filed in the Rubens documentation.
